text.tspan: In a double-blind experiment to assess whether aspirin helped stroke patients, 155
were randomised to receive either aspirin or a placebo for 6 months. After this time,
a doctor classified the progress of each patient as favourable or unfavourable.
Does aspirin increase the probability of a stroke patient making
There is very strong evidence that stroke patients are more likely to
make favourable progress after 6 months if they take aspirin.
